<p>The power of a simple, heartfelt message should not be underestimated.  A brief expression of sympathy can carry immense weight, offering the grieving a sense of being remembered and understood. Proper etiquette dictates that messages should be delivered promptly, ideally within a week of the loss, and should avoid overly long or verbose expressions.  Focus on genuine emotion and personal connection over elaborate wording.  The goal is to provide comfort and a sense of shared sorrow, helping the bereaved navigate their grief.</p>
    

